### Install Playwright using npm, yarn, or pnpm

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/intro-js.md

These commands initialize a new Playwright project or add Playwright to an existing one. The process prompts for configuration details like TypeScript/JavaScript preference, test folder name, GitHub Actions setup, and browser installation.

```bash
npm init playwright@latest
```

```bash
yarn create playwright
```

```bash
pnpm create playwright
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Project Dependencies for Global Setup in Playwright Config

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-global-setup-teardown-js.md

Defines a setup project named 'setup db' that matches the global.setup.ts file and configures another project to depend on it. This approach allows global setup to run before other tests while producing traces and artifacts that appear in HTML reports.

```javascript
import { defineConfig, devices } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  testDir: './tests',
  // ...
  projects: [
    {
      name: 'setup db',
      testMatch: /global\.setup\.ts/,
    },
    {
      name: 'chromium with db',
      use: { ...devices['Desktop Chrome'] },
      dependencies: ['setup db'],
    },
  ]
});
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Playwright Global Setup and Storage State (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-global-setup-teardown-js.md

This configuration file sets up Playwright to use a global setup script and defines the base URL and storage state file for tests. It's essential for enabling the global setup functionality.

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';
export default defineConfig({
  globalSetup: require.resolve('./global-setup'), // Path to the global setup file
  use: {
    baseURL: 'http://localhost:3000/', // Base URL for tests
    storageState: 'state.json', // File to store authentication state
  },
});
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Project Dependencies for Global Setup in Playwright

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-api/class-testproject.md

Shows how to configure project dependencies to ensure setup tasks run before test execution. The setup project runs global.setup.ts first, followed by browser-specific projects (chromium, firefox, webkit) that depend on it. Dependencies enable setup actions to produce traces, artifacts, and appear in test reports while maintaining test-like structure.

```javascript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  projects: [
    {
      name: 'setup',
      testMatch: /global.setup\.ts/,
    },
    {
      name: 'chromium',
      use: devices['Desktop Chrome'],
      dependencies: ['setup'],
    },
    {
      name: 'firefox',
      use: devices['Desktop Firefox'],
      dependencies: ['setup'],
    },
    {
      name: 'webkit',
      use: devices['Desktop Safari'],
      dependencies: ['setup'],
    },
  ],
});
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Global Setup and Teardown Using Config Options - TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-global-setup-teardown-js.md

Alternative approach to configure global setup and teardown using globalSetup and globalTeardown configuration properties. This method runs setup once before all tests and teardown once after all tests, but has limited features compared to project dependencies. The paths must resolve to modules that export setup/teardown functions.

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  globalSetup: require.resolve('./global-setup'),
  globalTeardown: require.resolve('./global-teardown'),
});
```

--------------------------------

### Define Playwright Test Project Dependencies for Setup (JavaScript/TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-projects-js.md

This configuration illustrates how to set up project dependencies in Playwright. A 'setup' project runs first, and then 'chromium', 'firefox', and 'webkit' projects depend on it, ensuring setup actions complete before browser-specific tests begin. This allows for global setup actions like logging in or database setup.

```js
import { defineConfig, devices } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  projects: [
    {
      name: 'setup',
      testMatch: '**/*.setup.ts',
    },
    {
      name: 'chromium',
      use: { ...devices['Desktop Chrome'] },
      dependencies: ['setup'],
    },
    {
      name: 'firefox',
      use: { ...devices['Desktop Firefox'] },
      dependencies: ['setup'],
    },
    {
      name: 'webkit',
      use: { ...devices['Desktop Safari'] },
      dependencies: ['setup'],
    },
  ],
});
```

