### Set up Playwright .NET console project and install browsers

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/library-csharp.md

This script demonstrates how to create a new .NET console application, add the `Microsoft.Playwright` NuGet package, build the project, and then install the necessary browser drivers using the Playwright PowerShell script. Ensure PowerShell is up-to-date if encountering `TypeNotFound` errors.

```bash
dotnet new console -n PlaywrightDemo
cd PlaywrightDemo

dotnet add package Microsoft.Playwright
dotnet build
pwsh bin/Debug/netX/playwright.ps1 install

dotnet tool update --global PowerShell
```

