### Set Environment Variables in Playwright Global Setup (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-global-setup-teardown-js.md

This global setup example shows how to set environment variables that can be accessed within Playwright tests. It demonstrates setting simple string data and JSON stringified data.

```typescript
import type { FullConfig } from '@playwright/test';

async function globalSetup(config: FullConfig) {
  process.env.FOO = 'some data';
  // Or a more complicated data structure as JSON:
  process.env.BAR = JSON.stringify({ some: 'data' });
}

export default globalSetup;
```

