### Configure React Router with beforeMount Hook in Playwright Component Testing

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-components-js.md

Demonstrates how to use the beforeMount hook to conditionally wrap a React component with BrowserRouter based on hooks configuration. The HooksConfig type enables routing configuration to be passed from test files, allowing flexible router setup during component mounting.

```typescript
import { beforeMount, afterMount } from '@playwright/experimental-ct-react/hooks';
import { BrowserRouter } from 'react-router-dom';

export type HooksConfig = {
  enableRouting?: boolean;
}

beforeMount<HooksConfig>(async ({ App, hooksConfig }) => {
  if (hooksConfig?.enableRouting)
    return <BrowserRouter><App /></BrowserRouter>;
});
```

