### Configure Vue Router with beforeMount Hook in Playwright Component Testing

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-components-js.md

Demonstrates how to use the beforeMount hook to conditionally add a Vue router to the app instance based on hooks configuration. The HooksConfig type enables routing configuration to be passed from test files for flexible router setup.

```typescript
import { beforeMount, afterMount } from '@playwright/experimental-ct-vue/hooks';
import { router } from '../src/router';

export type HooksConfig = {
  enableRouting?: boolean;
}

beforeMount<HooksConfig>(async ({ app, hooksConfig }) => {
  if (hooksConfig?.enableRouting)
    app.use(router);
});
```

