### Access Environment Variables in Playwright Tests (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-global-setup-teardown-js.md

This test file illustrates how to access environment variables that were previously set in the global setup. It verifies that the environment variables `FOO` and `BAR` are correctly populated and accessible.

```typescript
import { test } from '@playwright/test';

test('test', async ({ page }) => {
  // environment variables which are set in globalSetup are only available inside test().
  const { FOO, BAR } = process.env;

  // FOO and BAR properties are populated.
  expect(FOO).toEqual('some data');

  const complexData = JSON.parse(BAR);
  expect(complexData).toEqual({ some: 'data' }); // Corrected to check parsed JSON
});
```
